  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dda\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0db3\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca : \"\u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2 \u0d8b\u0db9\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0db6\u0ddd\u0db0\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0da2\u0dcf \u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dca\u0db6\"",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Tear gas for Antare: \"We had Bodhi Puja for you\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The police fired tear gas and water cannons at the protest that came from Kelaniya to Colombo on June 8, demanding that the President and the Prime Minister should step down and the activists in custody should be released.",
        "While protests are scheduled to be held in many areas including Colombo on July 09, the police headquarters (July 08) imposed a police curfew covering all police jurisdictions of 7 police divisions in the Western Province from 9 p.m. until further notice.",
        "A notice issued with the signature of the Inspector General of Police states that police curfew will be in effect in Colombo North, Colombo South, Colombo Central, Galkissa, Nugegoda, Kelaniya and Migomuwa police divisions until further notice.",
        "Many people are paying attention to the implementation of police curfew in a background where protests will be organized in Colombo tomorrow as a national day of protest, forcing President Gotabaya Rajapaksa and Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe to step down."
      ],
